$interpreted: Naya: What kind of stupid plan was that? Can't trust that so-called "strategist" after all!
Angelia: Looks like we have no choice but to use him as a hostage and brute force our way through the blockade.
Fredrica: Stop right there!
Fredrica: My my, what a jackpot~ Didn't think that my lost child will end up in the hands of the runaway princess~
Naya: Don't be a smart-ass. Move out of the way, or this guy is dead meat!
Fredrica: Can't do that~ I'm lazy on my days off, but when it's time to work, I'm always business~
Fredrica: Attention men. We have two missions: capture the princess and rescue the officer. Let's achieve them both with flying colors!
Angelia: We can't win. Naya, let's fall back!
Fredrica: Damn it, how dare you screw with me!
Jerome: ... Cough, cough...
Fredrica: You alright, handsome?
Jerome: I'm fine... where's traitor Angelia?
Fredrica: She got away.
Jerome: It's okay; I know where she is hiding.
Fredrica: Really!?
Jerome: When I was tied up, I heard them mention the location of their camp.
Fredrica: Is that so? You just made quite the contribution, handsome fella.
Fredrica: Summon all the forces we have nearby, as many as possible. This time, no one is getting away!
Bandit Leader: ... You've confirmed that the brats are safe. Where's the ransom!
Hyde: Didn't I say that the ransom is with my companion and we have to wait for them to get here?
Bandit Leader: Then when are they getting here?
Hyde: It's a large amount of money; makes sense that it takes some time to prepare~
Bandit Leader: Tch, wasting my time. I'll kill your a** first then sell these brats!
Bandit: Boss, his companions are here!
Hyde: Hmph~ looks like you get to live another day.
Hyde: Did you do everything just as I instructed?
Angelia: Yes, all is well.
Bandit Leader: They don't seem to have brought a lot of money. What kind of sneaky tricks are you playing?
Hyde: These two are maids of the princess of Kingdom of the Sun.
Hyde: Escort them to Sunshine Infantry; princess will give you a hefty reward. Voila, you have your money. See, quite simple, isn't it?
Bandit Leader: Are you stupid? Everyone and their mothers know that the princess is butting heads with Theodore! Why would I p*** off Theodore for no reason?
Hyde: It seems... that you don't have a choice anyways~
Fredrica: Charge!
Bandit Guard: The Kingdom Army just brought enough men to fill up half of Paradise Prairie and they're now heading straight for us!
Bandit Leader: What!? Why!? We didn't do anything that would p*** them off, did we?

Hyde: It could be a leak of mis-information.
They thought this is a rebel stronghold of some sort, so they dispatched an army to wipe it out~
Bandit Leader: What the hell does that have anything to do with me? This place looks nothing like a rebel stronghold no matter how you look at it!
Hyde: But, if they break in and see the princess's maids here, you'll be in some pretty serious trouble.
Bandit Leader: ...Damn it, you did it on purpose!

Hyde: So what~
Against the kingdom's elite forces, I wonder how long your men can hold?
Bandit Leader: Then I'll kill you all to prove that I have nothing to do with the rebels!

Hyde: If that solves the problem then sure...
BUT, are you sure that they'll take your word for it?
Bandit: Waaah! There are no princesses here. Spare our lives!

Fredrica: Loyal indeed, still guarding Angelia to this point!
Listen up, men! Crush whoever's in your way; leave no stone unturned until you find the princess!
Bandit Guard: Boss, what do we do now?
Bandit Leader: This...umm...I...
Hyde: You have no choices left. Right now, you only have one way out of this.
Bandit Leader: What?
Hyde: Give up your men and camp. While the army is stalled here, you escort these two back to Sunshine Infantry and ask the princess to return the favor!
Bandit Leader: Give up my camp? Are you telling me to flush years of hard work right down the drain?
Hyde: Ask the princess for a massive reward, you will still have the chance to come back. Get nailed by the unreasonable Kingdom Army, we're all screwed!
Hyde: There's no time left. Make your decision now!
Bandit Leader: Son of a *****, I'm definitely asking for a king's ransom when I see that princess!
Hyde: Looks like a decision has been made. Don't take too many men with you though. I say just these two young fellas would be fine.

Bandit Leader: You two, protect me on the way out.
Women and you ya crafty bastard, follow me!
